{#
  TABLE screen — INLINE EDITING OVERVIEW
  =====================================

  This template renders all nodes as a flat table (requirements and sections).
  By default the table is in display (read-only) mode.

  ACTIVATING EDIT MODE
  ---------------------
  The toolbar button [data-testid="table-toolbar-edit-btn"] toggles edit mode.
  Clicking it adds the CSS class "table--is-editable" to <table> (not in use),
  and [data-mode="edit"] to .main container.
  CSS rules in table_view.css make editable cells show cursor:pointer and a
  hover outline — only when that class is present.

  CELL EDITING MODES  (data-field-type attribute on <td>)
  --------------------------------------------------------
  "singleline"
      JS fetches the inline form from the URL stored in data-url attribute
      (GET /actions/table/get_node_singleline_inline).
      Server returns a turbo-stream that replaces the cell content with a
      single-line contenteditable form. On blur / outside click: JS POSTs the
      form to /actions/table/update_node_field, server updates
      <div id="cell-{mid}-{field}"> via turbo-stream.

  "multiline"
      JS fetches the inline form from the URL stored in data-url attribute
      (GET /actions/table/get_node_contenteditable_inline).
      Server returns a turbo-stream that replaces the cell content with a
      multi-line contenteditable form. On blur / outside click: JS POSTs the
      form to /actions/table/update_node_field_multiline, server updates
      <div id="cell-{mid}-{field}"> via turbo-stream.

  "comments"
      JS fetches /actions/table/get_node_comments_inline?node_mid=...
      Server returns an inline form with multiple comment fields.
      On blur / outside click: JS POSTs the form, server updates
      <div id="cell-{mid}-COMMENT"> via turbo-stream.

  "relations"
      JS fetches /actions/table/get_node_relations_inline?node_mid=...
      Server returns an inline form with relation rows (editable) and
      computed/derived relations (read-only).
      On blur / outside click: JS POSTs the form, server updates
      <div id="cell-{mid}-RELATIONS"> via turbo-stream.

  "autocomplete"
      A Stimulus controller (autocompletable) is already present in the DOM.
      Edit mode CSS hides .cell-display and shows .cell-edit-ac (contenteditable).
      On blur: JS POSTs to /actions/table/update_node_field via fetch.

  JS handles "singleline", "multiline", "comments", "relations" identically
  (openInlineCell / saveInlineCell). The distinction is purely server-side:
  different GET endpoints inject different form shapes; different POST endpoints
  process them.

  CELL EDITABILITY (is_table_cell_editable / get_table_cell_edit_mode)
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------
  Whether a field is editable depends on the document grammar for that node
  type. view_object.is_table_cell_editable() returns True if the field is
  declared in the grammar. get_table_cell_edit_mode() returns the Python grammar
  value: "autocomplete" | "singleline" | "multiline" | "readonly".
  td_by_edit_mode.jinja maps grammar values to data-field-type DOM attributes:
  "singleline" and "multiline" → data-field-type="contenteditable" (same component, server decides form shape).

  COLUMN VISIBILITY
  -----------------
  Columns are driven by view_object.enumerate_table_columns(),
  which yields only columns present in at least one grammar element.
  TYPE and LEVEL are always rendered as the two fixed first columns.
  When a column exists in the document grammar but a specific node's grammar
  does not declare that field, the cell gets the "content-view-td--dimmed" modifier.
#}
  <div class="main"
       js-pan_with_space="true"
       js-table_view_edit
  >
    {% include "_shared/tags.jinja.html" %}
      <div class="content">
        <div id="table-add-node-feedback" hidden></div>

        {# ================================================================ #}
        {# ROOT NODE / TITLE + META                                         #}
        {# similar: components/node_field/document_meta/index.jinja         #}
        {# ================================================================ #}
        {% include "screens/document/table/root_node.jinja" %}

        {# ================================================================ #}
        {# TABLE                                                            #}
        {# ================================================================ #}
        {#
          column_labels maps internal column IDs to display names.
          Dynamic fields (meta / non-reserved content) use their title as-is.
        #}
        {%- set column_labels = {
          "RELATIONS": "REFS",
          "TITLE":     "Title",
          "STATEMENT": "Statement",
          "RATIONALE": "Rationale",
          "COMMENT":   "Comment"
        } -%}
        {%- set content_entries = view_object.document_content_iterator() | list -%}
        <table class="content-view-table" js-table_view_edit-table>

          {# -- Header row ------------------------------------------------ #}
          <thead class="content-view-table_sticky-header">
            <tr>
              <th class="content-view-th" data-testid="col-header-Type">
                <div class="content-view-th__content">
                  <span class="content-view-th__label">Type</span>
                  <button class="content-view-th__sort-btn" aria-label="Sort by Type">{%- include "icons/ico16_sort.svg" -%}</button>
                </div>
              </th>
              <th class="content-view-th" data-testid="col-header-Level">
                <div class="content-view-th__content">
                  <span class="content-view-th__label">Level</span>
                  <button class="content-view-th__sort-btn" aria-label="Sort by Level">{%- include "icons/ico16_sort.svg" -%}</button>
                </div>
              </th>
              {%- for column in view_object.enumerate_table_columns() -%}
                {%- set col_label = column_labels.get(column, column) -%}
                <th class="content-view-th" data-testid="col-header-{{ col_label }}">
                  <div class="content-view-th__content">
                    <span class="content-view-th__label">{{ col_label }}</span>
                    <button class="content-view-th__sort-btn" aria-label="Sort by {{ col_label }}">{%- include "icons/ico16_sort.svg" -%}</button>
                  </div>
                </th>
              {%- endfor -%}
            </tr>
          </thead>

          {# -- Body rows ------------------------------------------------- #}
          {% include "screens/document/table/body.jinja" %}
        </table>
      </div>
      {# /.content #}
  </div>
  {# /.main #}
